<concept id="concept_nqg_fhl_v4">
  <title>Choosing an installer</title>
  <shortdesc/>
  <conbody>
    <p>You can install <ph keyref="product"/> on Linux using any of the following methods:</p>
    <ul>
      <li product="diff author developer editor svnClient">Install using the Linux installer, <ph
          keyref="executableInstallLinux"/>.</li>
      <li product="diff author developer editor svnClient">Install using the Linux installer in
        unattended mode.</li>
      <li product="diff author developer editor svnClient">Install from the archive <ph
          product="editor"><filepath>oxygen.tar.gz</filepath>
        </ph>
        <ph product="author">
          <filepath>oxygenAuthor.tar.gz</filepath>
        </ph><ph product="developer">
          <filepath>oxygenDeveloper.tar.gz</filepath>
        </ph>
        <ph product="diff">
          <filepath>oxygenXMLDiff.tar.gz</filepath>
        </ph>
        <ph product="svnClient">
          <filepath>syncroSVNClient.tar.gz</filepath>
        </ph> (the all platforms installer). Choose the all platforms installer if you have trouble
        installing using the Linux installer.</li>
      <li product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Install using the Update Site
        method.</li>
      <li product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">Install using the Zip archive
        method.</li>
    </ul>
  </conbody>
</concept>
